Accept": "text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "video_ext": "mp4", "audio_ext": "none", "abr": 0, "vbr": 391.247, "format": "dash-962648082943579v - 720x1280 (DASH video)"}], "title": "Video by missynovik", "description": "unpopular opinion", "duration": 355.433, "timestamp": 1774514730, "uploader_id": "1681882400", "uploader": "", "channel": "missynovik", "like_count": 143, "comment_count": 47, "comments": [{"author": "mahmoodhalawi", "author_id": "262585204", "id": "18180385957391165", "text": "That's definitely natural,, our creator made us like that , in islam male able to get more than one wife if it's necessary to him because we biologically able to love and connect with more than one women 🙂", "timestamp": 1775658368}, {"author": "noirrosemusic", "author_id": "7747411245", "id": "17853054507641763", "text": "Are you still looking for music producers btw?", "timestamp": 1775322861}, {"author": "tonyg242", "author_id": "329696919", "id": "17956105533110042", "text": "A man should only be married to ONE woman and ONE woman only . ONE is enough. This is the way it should be.", "timestamp": 1775173140}, {"author": "michaelnolan7894", "author_id": "4992829980", "id": "18098428549975651", "text": "Your a beautiful person", "timestamp": 1775069785}, {"author": "ganzenbes", "author_id": "43395659667", "id": "17885391177471833", "text": "Interesting thought. However if what you say is true women would not have pleasure which is not the case. The pleasure aspect is built in in men as well as women.", "timestamp": 1775035168}, {"author": "frank.oliveira87", "author_id": "79991243110", "id": "18103346614736139", "text": "@missynovik you're actually correct Biblically, 1 Timothy 3:2 & 12 makes the point that only men who are looking for a position of leadership in the Church should have just one wife. But the Apostle Paul didn't apply that rule to other men who were NOT looking to have a position of leadership in the Church. This sister gives a much more thorough explanation @kenzie_rose_s", "timestamp": 1774997652}, {"author": "xander_420_710", "author_id": "664125867", "id": "18110887903691526", "text": "The idea of being with multiple women is somewhat disheartening to me. That's definitely not what I want, I want to find my one and only.", "timestamp": 1774821771}, {"author": "hessgarymichael", "author_id": "63959250245", "id": "17916427173322044", "text": "I would like to procreate with you.", "timestamp": 1774664319}, {"author": "orglarovin", "author_id": "48698418", "id": "17858237133625467", "text": "Don't know if I'm heard through the noise @missynovik but you are essentially correct. But the female is not a passive part in this biologically. The main motive for the primate female is to secure strong genes AND that the offspring is provided for. Males exist on a spectrum from the alpha males to the caring males. So primate females (this has been shown in many studies both human and other primates) tend to partner with a caring male while mating with alpha males in secrecy.. in that fashion she can ensure good genes while maintaining a caretaker male who is confused or lures into that the offspring is his genes, and protective of an offspring that might not be his. So females have a strong drive for multiple unknown partners too... Biologically speaking. Whether this is a good model in modern society is something to argue about - but it's altogether prevalent 😂 for us humans.", "timestamp": 1774655732}], "thumbnails": [{"url": "https://scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.71878-15/656372499_1582979392785857_1257457126187448686_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6ImltYWdlX3VybGdlbi42NDB4MTEzNi5zZHIuZjcxODc4Lm5mcmFtZV9jb3Zlcl9mcmFtZS5jMiJ9&_nc_ht=scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=105&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gFVMJhHPJIXfsu7SWFpQMmKHMdW2j9GHlc5R7viqN2aM64fh27G3Zku4lhvJDSf2sU&_nc_ohc=